    "PostedDate": "2009-07-08T07:00:31.453-07:00",
    "UserRole": null,
    "MarkedAsAnswerDate": null
  },
  {
    "Id": "210221",
    "ThreadId": "28522",
    "Html": "<p>Nolan,</p>\r\n<p>You could always create your own RegionAdapter specifically for the TabControl that handles the setting of the tab header in code behind. This is overly involved and not particularly elegant in my opinion.</p>\r\n<p>If you redownload my sample I have updated it to do exactly what you are describing with WPF styles.</p>\r\n<p>Cheers</p>\r\n<p>Justin<br><a href=\"http://jtango.wordpress.com\">http://jtango.wordpress.com</a></p>",
    "PostedDate": "2009-07-08T17:44:46.087-07:00",
    "UserRole": null,
    "MarkedAsAnswerDate": null
